ore to the doctor with the agate eyes that he was not playing chess — he had merely set out the pieces once on a pocket board and glanced at two or three games printed in the newspapers — simply for lack of something to do. And even these lapses had not been his fault, but represented a series of moves in the general combination that was skillfully repeating an enigmatic theme.

